{"title_page": "Mater Dei Catholic College", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2015}}\n{{Use Australian English|date=April 2015}}\n{{Infobox school\n| name            = Mater Dei Catholic College\n| image           = Mater Dei Catholic College.jpg\n| size            = 240\n| motto           = Live God's message\n| established     = {{start date and age|2003|12}}<ref name=\"KayHull\">{{cite press release |author=Hull, Kay |author-link=Kay Hull |title=HULL OPENS MATER DEI CATHOLIC COLLEGE |url=http://www.kayhull.com.au/media/OpeningMaterDeiCatholicCollege111203.PDF |date=11 December 2003 |publisher=Member for Riverina, Kay Hull |accessdate=1 April 2008 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080722113918/http://www.kayhull.com.au/media/OpeningMaterDeiCatholicCollege111203.PDF |archive-date=22 July 2008 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n| type            = [[Independent school|Independent]] [[Mixed-sex education|co-educational]] [[Secondary school|secondary]] [[day school]]\n| denomination    = [[Roman Catholicism in Australia|Roman Catholic]]\n| oversight       = [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Wagga Wagga]]\n| slogan          = \n| principal       = Val Thomas<ref>{{cite web |title=Sacred Heart Parish |url=http://web.shk.wagga.catholic.edu.au/LinkClick.aspx?link=3155&tabid=2940&mid=6173 |publisher=Sacred Heart Primary School |accessdate=1 April 2008 }}{{Dead link|date=March 2020 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>\n| grades          = [[Year 7|7]]-[[Year 12|12]]\n| grades_label    = Years\n| location        = [[Wagga Wagga, New South Wales|Wagga Wagga]], [[New South Wales]]\n| country         = Australia\n| coordinates     = {{Coord|-35.17551|147.36376|region:AU-NSW_type:edu|display=inline,title|format=dms}}\n| pushpin_map             = Australia New South Wales\n| pushpin_image           = \n| pushpin_mapsize         = 240\n| pushpin_map_alt         = \n| pushpin_map_caption     = Location in [[New South Wales]]\n| pushpin_label           = \n| pushpin_label_position  = \n| enrolment       = \n| staff           = \n| colours         = Maroon, navy blue, yellow and white {{colorbox|maroon}}{{colorbox|navy}}{{colorbox|yellow}}{{colorbox|white}}\n| website         = {{URL|mdccww.catholic.edu.au}}\n|module={{Infobox mapframe\n|stroke-colour=#C60C30\n|stroke-width=3\n|marker=school\n|marker-colour=#1F2F57\n|zoom=13\n}}\n}}\n\n'''Mater Dei Catholic College''' is an [[Independent school|independent]] [[Roman Catholicism in Australia|Roman Catholic]] [[Mixed-sex education|co-educational]] [[Secondary school|secondary]] [[day school]] catering for students in [[Year 7]] to [[Year 12]], located in the [[Wagga Wagga, New South Wales|Wagga Wagga]] suburb of {{NSWcity|Lake Albert}}, in [[New South Wales]], Australia.<ref name=\"MaterDei\">{{cite web |title=Our College |url=http://www.mdcc.wagga.catholic.edu.au |publisher=Mater Dei Catholic College |accessdate=1 April 2008 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080718164104/http://www.mdcc.wagga.catholic.edu.au/ |archive-date=18 July 2008 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\n== History ==\nMater Dei Catholic College was established in 2003 by [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Wagga Wagga|Wagga Wagga Diocesan]] Catholic Schools Office as part of the decision in 1999 to establish two Catholic co-educational colleges from Years 7 to 12. Prior to this, there was two 7-10 Catholic High schools, one for boys (Saint Michael's Regional High School, Wagga) and one for girls (Mount Erin High School, Wagga). Then, in years 11 and 12, both schools merged to Trinity Senior High School, located at the current site of [[Kildare Catholic College]], Wagga. \n\n== Overview ==\n\nThe school is a Catholic secondary school in the Wagga Wagga Denerary and Diocese. It has five houses which are each named after significant people in the College's history. Kennedy (Blue), after Graham Kennedy, Rosarie (Red), after Sister Rosarie, Webber (Green), after Sister Webber, Caroll (Purple) House after Bishop Carroll and Sherrin (Gold) after Brother Carl Sherrin, principal of Trinity Senior High from 1988\u20131993.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://web.mdccww.catholic.edu.au/house-system/sherrin-house |work=Mater Dei Catholic College |title=Sherin House |accessdate=14 March 2018 |date=n.d. }}</ref>\n\n==Principals==\nThe following individuals have served as College Principal:\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Ordinal !! Officeholders !! Term start !! Term end !! Time in office !! Notes\n|-  \n|align=center| {{nts|1}} || Clem Welch ||align=center| 2004 ||align=center| 2007 ||align=right| {{age in years|2004|2007}} years ||\n|-  \n|align=center| {{nts|2}} || Greg Miller ||align=center| 2008 ||align=center| 2014 ||align=right| {{age in years|2008|2014}} years ||\n|-  \n|align=center| {{nts|3}} || Val Thomas ||align=center| 2015 ||align=center| ''incumbent'' ||align=right| {{age in years|2015}} years ||\n|}\n\n== See also ==\n{{stack|{{portal|New South Wales|Schools|Catholicism}}}}\n* [[List of Catholic schools in New South Wales]]\n* [[List of schools in the Riverina]]\n* [[Catholic education in Australia]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Catholic secondary schools in New South Wales]]\n[[Category:Educational institutions established in 2003]]\n[[Category:2003 establishments in Australia]]\n[[Category:Education in Wagga Wagga]]\n[[Category:Roman Catholic Diocese of Wagga Wagga]]\n\n\n{{Australia-school-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2015}}\n{{Use Australian English|date=April 2015}}\n{{Infobox school\n| name            = Mater Dei Catholic College\n| image           = Mater Dei Catholic College.jpg\n| size            = 240\n| motto           = Live God's message\n| established     = {{start date and age|2003|12}}<ref name=\"KayHull\">{{cite press release |author=Hull, Kay |author-link=Kay Hull |title=HULL OPENS MATER DEI CATHOLIC COLLEGE |url=http://www.kayhull.com.au/media/OpeningMaterDeiCatholicCollege111203.PDF |date=11 December 2003 |publisher=Member for Riverina, Kay Hull |accessdate=1 April 2008 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080722113918/http://www.kayhull.com.au/media/OpeningMaterDeiCatholicCollege111203.PDF |archive-date=22 July 2008 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n| type            = [[Independent school|Independent]] [[Mixed-sex education|co-educational]] [[Secondary school|secondary]] [[day school]]\n| denomination    = [[Roman Catholicism in Australia|Roman Catholic]]\n| oversight       = [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Wagga Wagga]]\n| slogan          = \n| principal       = Val Thomas<ref>{{cite web |title=Sacred Heart Parish |url=http://web.shk.wagga.catholic.edu.au/LinkClick.aspx?link=3155&tabid=2940&mid=6173 |publisher=Sacred Heart Primary School |accessdate=1 April 2008 }}{{Dead link|date=March 2020 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>\n| grades          = [[Year 7|7]]-[[Year 12|12]]\n| grades_label    = Years\n| location        = [[Wagga Wagga, New South Wales|Wagga Wagga]], [[New South Wales]]\n| country         = Australia\n| coordinates     = {{Coord|-35.17551|147.36376|region:AU-NSW_type:edu|display=inline,title|format=dms}}\n| pushpin_map             = Australia New South Wales\n| pushpin_image           = \n| pushpin_mapsize         = 240\n| pushpin_map_alt         = \n| pushpin_map_caption     = Location in [[New South Wales]]\n| pushpin_label           = \n| pushpin_label_position  = \n| enrolment       = \n| staff           = \n| colours         = Maroon, navy blue, yellow and white {{colorbox|maroon}}{{colorbox|navy}}{{colorbox|yellow}}{{colorbox|white}}\n| website         = {{URL|mdccww.catholic.edu.au}}\n|module={{Infobox mapframe\n|stroke-colour=#C60C30\n|stroke-width=3\n|marker=school\n|marker-colour=#1F2F57\n|zoom=13\n}}\n}}\n\n'''Mater Dei Catholic College''' is an [[Independent school|independent]] [[Roman Catholicism in Australia|Roman Catholic]] [[Mixed-sex education|co-educational]] [[Secondary school|secondary]] [[day school]] catering for students in [[Year 7]] to [[Year 12]], located in the [[Wagga Wagga, New South Wales|Wagga Wagga]] suburb of {{NSWcity|Lake Albert}}, in [[New South Wales]], Australia.<ref name=\"MaterDei\">{{cite web |title=Our College |url=http://www.mdcc.wagga.catholic.edu.au |publisher=Mater Dei Catholic College |accessdate=1 April 2008 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080718164104/http://www.mdcc.wagga.catholic.edu.au/ |archive-date=18 July 2008 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\n== History ==\nMater Dei Catholic College was established in 2003 by [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Wagga Wagga|Wagga Wagga Diocesan]] Catholic Schools Office as part of the decision in 1999 to establish two Catholic co-educational colleges from Years 7 to 12. Prior to this, there was two 7-10 Catholic High schools, one for boys (Saint Michael's Regional High School, Wagga) and one for girls (Mount Erin High School, Wagga). Then, in years 11 and 12, both schools merged to Trinity Senior High School, located at the current site of [[Kildare Catholic College]], Wagga. \n\n== Overview ==\n\nThe school is a Catholic secondary school in the Wagga Wagga Denerary and Diocese. It has five houses which are each named after significant people in the College's history. Kennedy (Blue), after Graham Kennedy, Rosarie (Red), after Sister Rosarie, Webber (Green), after Sister Webber, Caroll (Purple) House after Bishop Carroll and Sherrin (Gold) after Brother Carl Sherrin, principal of Trinity Senior High from 1988\u20131993.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://web.mdccww.catholic.edu.au/house-system/sherrin-house |work=Mater Dei Catholic College |title=Sherin House |accessdate=14 March 2018 |date=n.d. }}</ref>\n\n==Principals==\nThe following individuals have served as College Principal:\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Ordinal !! Officeholders !! Term start !! Term end !! Time in office !! Notes\n|-  \n|align=center| {{nts|1}} || Clem Welch ||align=center| 2004 ||align=center| 2007 ||align=right| {{age in years|2004|2007}} years |