e web |title=General Mosconi Airport |url=https://www.google.com/maps/@-22.6155385,-63.7940761,3463m/data=!3m1!1e3 |website=Google Maps |publisher=Google |accessdate=18 April 2019}}</ref>\n}}\n \n'''Tartagal Airport \u2013 General Enrique Mosconi'''  ({{lang-es|link=no|Aeropuerto de Tartagal \u2013 Gral. Enrique Mosconi}}) {{airport codes|TTG|SAST}} is an airport serving [[Tartagal, Salta|Tartagal]], a city in the [[Salta Province]] of [[Argentina]]. It is located {{convert|2|km|0}} from the town of [[General Mosconi, Salta|General Mosconi]], and {{convert|9|km}} south of Tartagal. The airport was named after the Argentine military engineer [[Enrique Mosconi]].\n\nThe runway length includes a {{convert|260|m}} [[displaced threshold]] on Runway 20. The Tartagal [[non-directional beacon]] (Ident: '''TAR''') is located {{convert|1.5|nmi|km|0}} west-southwest of the airport.<ref>{{cite web |title=Tartagal NDB |url=http://ourairports.com/navaids/TAR/Tartagal_NDB_AR/ |website=Our Airports |accessdate=19 April 2019}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n*{{portal-inline|Argentina}}\n*{{portal-inline|Aviation}}\n*[[Transport in Argentina]]\n*[[List of airports in Argentina]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[https://www.openstreetmap.org/#map=13/-22.6230/-63.7909 OpenStreetMap - General Mosconi Airport]\n*[http://fallingrain.com/icao/SAST.html FallingRain - General Enrique Mosconi Airport]\n*{{GCM|TTG|General Enrique Mosconi Tartagal Airport}}\n*{{ASN|TTG}}\n\n{{Airports in Argentina}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Airports in Argentina]]\n\n\n{{Argentina-airport-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{distinguish|General Enrique Mosconi Airport}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2014}}\n{{Infobox airport\n| name         = Tartagal Airport\n| nativename   = General Enrique Mosconi Airport\n| nativename-a =\n| nativename-r =\n| image        =\n| image-width  = <!-- if less than 200 -->\n| caption      =\n| image2       =\n| image2-width = <!-- if less than 200 -->\n| caption2   