|km|2|abbr=on}}\n| valign=\"top\" | {{NZR sl|Heretaunga}}\n| valign=\"top\" | {{coord|41|08|32.37|S|175|01|33.20|E|type:railwaystation_region:NZ}}\n|\n| valign=\"top\" | This station serves the suburb of Heretaunga and was opened in 1908.\n|-\n| valign=\"top\" | {{convert|29.40|km|2|abbr=on}}\n| valign=\"top\" | {{NZR sl|Trentham|suffix=, New Zealand}}\n| valign=\"top\" | {{coord|41|08|15.76|S|175|02|19.09|E|type:railwaystation_region:NZ}}\n|\n| valign=\"top\" | This station serves the suburb of Trentham and was opened in 1907. It is the northern terminus of double-track operations on the Wairarapa Line.\n|-\n| valign=\"top\" | {{convert|31.30|km|2|abbr=on}}\n| valign=\"top\" | {{NZR sl|Wallaceville}}\n| valign=\"top\" | {{coord|41|07|50.82|S|175|03|29.30|E|type:railwaystation_region:NZ}}\n|\n| valign=\"top\" | This station serves the suburb of Wallaceville and was opened in 1879.\n|-\n| valign=\"top\" | {{convert|32.40|km|2|abbr=on}}\n| valign=\"top\" | {{NZR sl|Upper Hutt}}\n| valign=\"top\" | {{coord|41|7|34.11|S|175|4|13.77|E|type:railwaystation_region:NZ}}\n| [[:File:Upper Hutt railway station 02.JPG|Photo]]\n| valign=\"top\" | This station serves the city of Upper Hutt and was opened in 1876. It marks the northernmost extent of electric operations on the Wairarapa Line.\n|-\n| align=\"left\" colspan=5 |\n\n====Rimutaka Section====\nSection closed 30 October 1955; Rimutaka Deviation opened 3 November 1955\n|-\n! Distance from Wellington\n! Name\n! Location\n! Image\n! Notes\n|-\n|\n| valign=\"top\" | {{NZR sl|Mangaroa}}\n| valign=\"top\" | {{coord|41|7|16.58|S|175|6|37.48|E|type:railwaystation_region:NZ}}\n| [[:File:Mangaroa railway station 01.JPG|Photo]]\n| valign=\"top\" | One of the original stations on the Rimutaka section, this station served the small settlement of Mangaroa. Closed in 1955 along with the old route over the Rimutaka Range.\n|-\n|\n| valign=\"top\" | {{NZR sl|Kaitoke}}\n| valign=\"top\" | {{coord|41|5|4.22|S|175|10|5.02|E|type:railwaystatio