ice of Serbia |accessdate=1 January 2020 |language=Serbian |format=PDF}}</ref>\n| area_total_km2         = 32.70\n| area_land_km2          = \n| population_as_of       = 2011\n| population_footnotes   = <ref>{{Serbian census 2011}}</ref>\n| population_total       = 1955\n| population_density_km2 = auto\n| timezone               = [[Central European Time|CET]]\n| utc_offset             = +1\n| timezone_DST           = [[Central European Summer Time|CEST]]\n| utc_offset_DST         = +2\n| elevation_m            = 93\n| area_code              = \n| postal_code_type       = [[Postal code]]\n| postal_code            = 22 224\n}}\n\n'''Kukujevci''' ({{lang-sr-cyr|\u041a\u0443\u043a\u0443\u0458\u0435\u0432\u0446\u0438}}) is a village located in the municipality of [[\u0160id]], [[Srem District]], [[Vojvodina]], Serbia. As of 2011 census, it has a population of 1,955 inhabitants.\n\n==Name==\nThe name of the village in [[Serbian language|Serbian]] is in the plural, and therefore it is grammatically correct to refer to it as ''\"Kukujevci are\"'' instead of ''\"Kukujevci is\"''. A hypothetical singular version of the name would be ''Kukujevac''.\n\n==History==\n[[File:Kukujevci, rimokatoli\u010dka crkva 05.jpg|thumb|right|Roman Catholic Church in Kukujevci]]\nPrior to the [[Yugoslav Wars]], the population of the village was 89% [[Croat]].<ref>[http://www.aimpress.ch/dyn/pubs/archive/data/199506/50612-004-pubs-beo.htm 1995/06/12 22:25 GLAVOM U PESAK<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> During the Yugoslav Wars and particularly as a spillover from the [[Croatian War of Independence]] local Croat community in Kukujevci was exposed to harassment and persecution by Serbian nationalists leading to community's expulsion from the village.<ref name=\"Josipovi\u0107Kukujevci\">{{cite web |url=https://www.tportal.hr/vijesti/clanak/president-josipovic-visits-kukujevci-20110901 |last=Mati\u0107 |first=Dragan |title=President Josipovic visits Kukujevci |accessdate=31 August 2019 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190831190514/https://www.tportal.hr/vijesti/clanak/president-josipovic-visits-kukujevci-20110901 |archive-date=31 August 2019 }}</ref> As a consequence of the war demographic structure of the village is today almost entirely different with 90% of population being ethnic Serbs, mostly Serb refugees who left after the collapse of the self-proclaimed [[SAO Western Slavonia]] or from other parts of [[Croatia]].<ref name=\"VMKukujevci\">{{cite web |url=http://www.vm.rs/kukujevci-gde-slavonci-postadose-sremci/ |last=Tuci\u0107 |first=Ilija |title=Kukujevci \u2013 Gde Slavonci postado\u0161e Sremci |accessdate=31 August 2019 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190831192434/http://www.vm.rs/kukujevci-gde-slavonci-postadose-sremci/ |archive-date=31 August 2019 }}</ref> The new  Serbian population has sought to rename the village to ''Lazarevo''.<ref>[http://www.vecernji.hr/newsroom/news/international/2955187/index.do Croats in Vojvodina against the renaming of previous Croatian villages] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080118095749/http://www.vecernji.hr/newsroom/news/international/2955187/index.do |date=2008-01-18 }}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of places in Serbia]]\n* [[List of cities, towns and villages in Vojvodina]]\n* [[Kukujevci\u2013Erdevik railway station]]\n\n==References==\n{{commonscat|Kukujevci}}\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{\u0160id Municipality}}\n{{Srem District}}\n\n[[Category:Populated places in Syrmia]]\n\n{{SremRS-geo-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{infobox settlement\n| official_name          = Kukujevci\n| other_name             = \n| native_name            = {{native name|sr-Cyrl|\u041a\u0443\u043a\u0443\u0458\u0435\u0432\u0446\u0438|italics=off}}\n| native_name_lang       = sr\n| settlement_type        = [[List of populated places in Serbia|Village]] ([[village#Slavic countries|Selo]])\n| motto                  = \n| image_skyline          = \u041a\u0443\u043a\u0443\u0458\u0435\u0432\u0446\u0438 (\u043f\u0440\u0430\u0432\u043e\u0441\u043b\u0430\u0432\u043d\u0430 \u0446\u0440\u043a\u0432\u0430) - Kukujevci (orthodox church).JPG\n| imagesize              = \n| image_caption          = \n| image_flag             = \n| flag_size              = \n| image_seal             = \n| seal_size              = \n| image_map              = \n| mapsize                = \n| map_caption            = \n| subdivision_type        = [[List of sovereign states|Country]]\n| subdivision_name        = {{flag|Serbia}}\n| subdivision_type1       = [[Subdivisions of Serbia|Province]]\n| subdivision_name1       = {{flag|Vojvodina}}\n| subdivision_type2       = [[List of regions of Serbia|Region]]\n| subdivision_name2       = [[Syrmia]]\n| subdivision_type3       = [[Districts of Serbia|District]]\n| subdivision_name3       = [[Srem District|Srem]]\n| subdivision_type4       = [[Municipalities of Serbia|Municipality]]\n| subdivision_name4       = [[\u0160id]]\n| coordinates            = {{coord|45|04|N|19|20|E|display=inline,title}}\n| pushpin_map            = Serbia\n| pushpin_label_position = right\n| pushpin_mapsize        = \n| pushpin_map_caption    = \n| unit_pref              = Metric\n| area_footnotes         = <ref name=\"area-sid\">{{cite web |title=\u041d\u0430\u0441\u0435\u0459\u0430 \u043e\u043f\u0448\u0442\u0438\u043d\u0435 \u0428\u0438\u0434 |url=https://webrzs.stat.gov.rs/axd/Registar/SlikeRegioni/Mapiranemape/BG%20i%20VOJ/ReSid.pdf |website=stat.gov.rs |publisher=Statistical Office of Serbia |accessdate=1 January 2020 |language=Serbian |format=PDF}}</ref>\n| area_total_km2         = 32.70\n| area_land_km2          = \n| population_as_of       = 2011\n| population_footnotes   = <ref>{{Serbian census 2011}}</ref>\n| population_total       = 1955\n| population_density_km2 = auto\n| timezone               = [[Central European Time|CET]]\n| utc_offset             = +1\n| timezone_DST           = [[Central European Summer Time|CEST]]\n| utc_offset_DST         = +2\n| elevation_m            = 93\n| area_code              = \n| postal_code_type       = [[Postal code]]\n| postal_code            = 22 224\n}}\n\n'''Kukujevci''' ({{lang-sr-cyr|\u041a\u0443\u043a\u0443\u0458\u0435\u0432\u0446\u0438}}) is a village located int the municipality of [[\u0160id]], [[Srem District]], [[Vojvodina]], Serbia. As of 2011 census, it has a population of 1,955 inhabitants.\n\n==Name==\nThe name of the village in [[Serbian language|Serbian]] is in the plural, and therefore it is grammatically correct to refer to it as ''\"Kukujevci are\"'' instead of ''\"Kukujevci is\"''. A hypothetical singular version of the name would be ''Kukujevac''.\n\n==History==\n[[File:Kukujevci, rimokatoli\u010dka crkva 05.jpg|thumb|right|Roman Catholic Church in Kukujevci]]\nPrior to the [[Yugoslav Wars]], the population of the village was 89% [[Croat]].<ref>[http://www.aimpress.ch/dyn/pubs/archive/data/199506/50612-004-pubs-beo.htm 1995/06/12 22:25 GLAVOM U PESAK<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> During the Yugoslav Wars and particularly as a spillover from the [[Croatian War of Independence]] local Croat community in Kukujevci was exposed to harassment and persecution by Serbian nationalists leading to community's expulsion from the village.<ref name=\"Josipovi\u0107Kukujevci\">{{cite web |url=https://www.tportal.hr/vijesti/clanak/president-josipovic-visits-kukujevci-20110901 |last=Mati\u0107 |first=Dragan |title=President Josipovic visits Kukujevci |accessdate=31 August 2019 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190831190514/https://www.tportal.hr/vijesti/clanak/president-josipovic-visits-kukujevci-20110901 |archive-date=31 August 2019 }}</ref> As a consequence of the war demographic structure of the village is today almost entirely different with 90% of population being ethnic Serbs, mostly Serb refugees who left after the collapse of the self-proclaimed [[SAO Western Slavonia]] or from other parts of [[Croatia]].<ref name=\"VMKukujevci\">{{cite web |url=http://www.vm.rs/kukujevci-gde-slavonci-postadose-sremci/ |last=Tuci\u0107 |first=Ilija |title=Kukujevci \u2013 Gde Slavonci postado\u0161e Sremci |accessdate=31 August 2019 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190831192434/http://www.vm.rs/kukujevci-gde-slavonci-postadose-sremci/ |archive-date=31 August 2019 }}</ref> The new  Serbian population has sought to rename the village to ''Lazarevo''.<ref>[http://www.vecernji.hr/newsroom/news/international/2955187/index.do Croats in Vojvodina against the renaming of previous Croatian villages] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080118095749/http://www.vecernji.hr/newsroom/news/international/2955187/index.do |date=2008-01-18 }}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of places in Serbia]]\n* [[List of cities, towns and villages in Vojvodina]]\n* [[Kukujevci\u2013Erdevik railway station]]\n\n==References==\n{{commonscat|Kukujevci}}\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{\u0160id Municipality}}\n{{Srem District}}\n\n[[Category:Populated places in Syrmia]]\n\n{{SremRS-geo-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Reyk", "label": "safe", "comment": "typo", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kukujevci"}
